The Bloodied and Torn Journal Page Reads:

"I have requested permission of my father to marry this woman.  Though she is  beneath my station. There are things about her which are unlike any other woman that has ever come to this court! Still, I suspect her favorite necklace was a gift from a former lover... she seems quite sentimental about it, and never takes it off... I have given her other jewelry to wear, as well. I am hoping to find some way to win her back from this nostalgia that seems to have afflicted her recently."
